  "term": "prop:sup-char",
  "kind": "Proposition",
  "title": "Characterisation of Supremum",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $(A, \\leq)$ be a poset, $S \\subseteq A$, and $u^* \\in A$. Then\n$u^* = \\sup S$ if and only if:\n- [label=(\\roman*)]\n- $u^*$ is an upper bound of $S$; and\n- for every $v \\in A$ with $v < u^*$, there exists $s \\in S$ with\n $v < s$.",
